page.title: 14TRAFFIC COUNTS
page.content: We conducted two counts outside our School, one on a weekday and one on a Saturday. On the Thursday morning, 96 cars went by, two buses, a mobile bank, two bicycles and two foreign cars. We noticed that 22 cars went by twice. The registration numbers we collected showed that people come from all over the country to Robin Hoods Bay. In the afternoon 106 cars went by, two motorbikes, three vans, one taxi, two buses, two foreign cars and one tractor. On the Saturday morning we saw a car from Oman in Saudi Arabia. The registration number was written in Arabic. In the afternoon 96 English cars went by, two foreign cars and one motorbike. The total number of cars for the day was very much the same as the weekday.
